<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="58" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,839,1505]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,433,1358,1384]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Remarks.</emphasis>
Currently, both &quot; 
<emphasis box="[638,834,1359,1384]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Embrik­Strandia</emphasis>
&quot; and &quot; 
<taxonomicName box="[916,1100,1359,1384]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Embrikstrandia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[916,1100,1359,1384]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Embrikstrandia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; are being used as the name of the genus. However, according to the fourth edition (
<number box="[1059,1120,1399,1425]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1999.0">1999</number>
) of International Code of Zoological Nomenclature (http://www.iczn.org/iczn/), 
<taxonomicName box="[1014,1198,1439,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Embrikstrandia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1014,1198,1439,1464]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Embrikstrandia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be the proper name for the genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Heffern" box="[631,802,1479,1505]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67" refString="Heffern, D. J. (2005) Catalog and Bibliography of Longhorned Beetles from Borneo (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) - Electronic Version, 2005.1 Available from http: // www. zin. ru / animalia / coleoptera / eng / borneoce. htm (accessed 23 July 2006)" type="journal article" year="2005">
Heffern, 
<number box="[738,802,1479,1505]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
